{
  "stem": "13313.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But you know, like a blind person will-- will-- will develop his sense of hearing very acutely, so we-- I developed a sense of hearing because we were not supposed to hear or listen and to know.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So I heard everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so I heard the news, the BBC news.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Matter of fact, it came-- it came through and there was always these scrambling sounds.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You know, for instance, I remember in-- in-- in-- in German and in French and Dutch how the BBC used to say, here's the BBC.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "This is the radio of free Belgium, or free France.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then-- and then the scramble, boom, boom, boom, boom, boom, boom, boom.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And in between there would be the news.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "From that, I used to know everything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "As-- like today, like today, I'm aware of what's going on in the world.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I used to know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "From-- the Roggemans never knew that I heard or listened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I never gave away that I heard or listened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But somehow I had such a keen sense of hearing developed because of that, that I knew exactly what was going on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And the point that this is leading to is that 19-- 1943, in the fall when this all started, the Germans were at the height of their military power.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "That's when they were on their march.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The east front had been opened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they were moving towards Moscow and Stalingrad and Leningrad.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So every day on the news there was another Polish or Russian town being taken.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So all you heard on the news, today the-- the Germans took Smolensk and Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These names still ring in the back of my mind from those days because I remember those words.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
